file=AI & Agents/meta/custom/fleet-governance/assets/change-proposal-template.md · fcp:Fleet Change Proposal — <ID: FCP-YYYYMMDD-nn>=**Proposed by:** <agent> \· **Date:** <YYYY-MM-DD> \· **Type:** skill-edit \| new-agent \| retire-agent \| model-change \| threshold-change \| other\n**Routes to:** board (Governance Gate) — Fleet Charter Rail 3. No change applies before a verdict.\n · 1wc:1. What changes=<One paragraph. Name the exact artifact(s): file paths, agent names, registry entries.>\n · 2w(:2. Why (evidence)=<The observed problem or lesson. Cite: gauge scorecard line, incident report, audit finding, post-mortem, or operator request. "It seemed better" is not evidence.>\n · 3ed:3. Exact diff or spec=<For skill edits: before/after text of every changed section. For new agents: the full proposed shape per agent-architecture-standards. No "and related cleanups".>\n · 4r:4. Risk=<What could this break? Which agents consume the changed artifact? Confidence flag per rule 0.6: formula-verified or reasoning-based.>\n · 5r:5. Rollback=<The exact revert action. If not trivially revertible, say so — board weighs that.>\n · 6v(:6. Verdict (board fills in)=APPROVED / REJECTED / AMENDED (attach diff) \· Date \· Archived by precedent: <ref>\n